title: No Princess
lyrics: Once, far away and long ago Was a tale my daddy told, to me He said, theres a land of fantasy Theres a prince wholl fight for me, Till the end This isnt how I thought it was supposed to be You were the one who I imagined next to me But sometimes love fell in the hands of the wreckless This is no fairytale, and I am no princess Now, were living in the strangest dream I dont know what to believe Cuz when, you said, Im the one wholl find for you Im the one youll never lose That was just to tell This isn’t how I thought it was supposed to be You were the one who I imagined next to me But sometimes love fell in the hands of the wreckless This is no fairytale, and I am no princess If I am a prisoner then where is my captor And Ill never know happily ever after Thats just how it is But now Im wiser Next time Ill write my own last chapte eeeee eeer This isnt how I thought it was supposed to be You were the one who I imagined next to me But sometimes love fell in the hands of the wreckless This is no fairytale, and I am no princess
